cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes an algorithm for computing Euclidean projections onto non-convex sets characterized as intersections of a simplex and a hypersphere. This involves optimization and numerical analysis, which suggests the paper could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions previous methods that required sorting, which suggests it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm for computing the product of the gradient of the projection with an arbitrary vector, which suggests it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
